Cascading auto-discharge: discharge creates new obligations that also need discharging

SCENARIO: Database transaction pattern
  connect() → Connection[connected!]
  begin()   → Transaction[in_transaction!]  (consumes connected)
  commit()  → Connection[connected!]        (consumes in_transaction, CREATES connected!)
  close()   → void                          (consumes connected)

CURRENT LIMITATION:
  [!] annotation only allowed on void events (no branches)
  commit has | committed branch, so can't be marked [!]

REQUIRED CHANGES:
  1. Allow [!] on single-branch events (not just void)
  2. When discharging single-branch event, track new obligations from output
  3. Run auto-discharge iteratively until no obligations remain

USER BENEFIT:
  Write only the happy path, compiler handles cleanup cascade:
    ~connect() | connected _ |>
        begin(conn: _.conn) | begun _ |>
            do_work(tx: _.tx) | done _ |> _

  Compiler auto-inserts: commit(tx) then close(conn)
